        "title": "Listening for Log Messages in slf4j/logback",
        "body": "<p>I have a Swing-based application without a console that logs all messages to text files through slf4j with logback underneath.<\/p>\n\n<p>Whenever a message is logged, I'd also like to add it to a <code>JTextArea<\/code> for the end user to see on the screen.<\/p>\n\n<p>These messages should be formatted the sameway as the log files for consistency. <\/p>\n\n<p>Does slf4j/logback have API that lets you add a listener for log messages so that I can copy them to <code>JTextArea<\/code>? <\/p>\n",
